{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|彥|頁|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=head}}.

Bronze inscription forms: {{Han compound|产|面|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=face}}.

===Etymology===
Various possibilities exist:
* Related to {{och-l|額|forehead}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}});
* From {{och-l|迓|to receive; to welcome}} + nominalising suffix *''-n'' ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{cog|bo|ངར||front side}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
* From a root {{m|und|*ŋ(ˤ)rar||slope, nearly vertical side}}, whence also {{och-l|涯|river bank|tr=*ŋˤrar}}, {{och-l|巘|hill|tr=*ŋ(r)ar(ʔ)}}, & {{och-l|山|tr=*s-ŋrar|mountain}} ({{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart, 2014}}).
* Cognate with {{cog|sit-jap|tɯ'''rŋa'''||face}}, {{cog|jiq|-}} ''rŋá'' ({{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai, 2019}}).

